---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Quoter"
  description="The terms for using Quoter's free roof estimates."
>
  <main class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="legal-panel rounded-3xl p-7 sm:p-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-[14px] font-medium text-brand-600 hover:underline">&larr; Back to Quoter</a>

      <h1 class="font-display mt-5 text-[clamp(1.9rem,5vw,2.6rem)] leading-[1.05] text-ink">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <h2>What Quoter is</h2>
      <p>
        Quoter gives you a free estimate for roofing work. You type in an
        address, we look at satellite imagery of the property, and we show you
        an estimated price range for the work.
      </p>

      <h2>Estimates are not final quotes</h2>
      <p>
        Every price Quoter shows you is a ballpark figure. It is there to help
        you plan and budget. It is not a contract, an offer, or a final price.
        A qualified local roofer confirms the exact price after inspecting the
        property, and only that confirmed price counts.
      </p>

      <h2>Using Quoter</h2>
      <p>
        Quoter is free to use. You agree to only request estimates for
        properties you own or have a genuine interest in, and not to use the
        service in a way that disrupts it for others.
      </p>

      <h2>Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        We work hard to make estimates useful, but satellite measurements and
        regional pricing have limits. We cannot guarantee accuracy, and we are
        not responsible for decisions made on the basis of an estimate alone.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:hello@quoter.app" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline">hello@quoter.app</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-panel {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(1.3);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(1.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-float);
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-top: 1.9rem;
  }
  p {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
</style>
